-- CTC Media’s TV Weekly Audience Falls in Russia, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-10-04T20:18:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/ctc-media-s-tv-weekly-audience-falls-in-russia-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers 18 years
and older fall in the week to Sept. 30, according to TNS-Global.  The share of Russian viewers aged 18 years and older for
CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source
of revenue, shrunk to 5.6 percent in the week to Sept. 30 from
5.7 percent in the week to Sept. 23, TNS-Global said by e-mail
today. CTC remained the sixth most-watched TV channel in the
week to Sept. 30.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over rose to 6.6 percent in the week to Sept. 30 from to 6.5
percent the previous week, the data show. CTC remained the fifth
most-watched TV channel among viewers 4 year and over in the
week to Sept. 30, the researcher said.  NTV Television, Rossiya-1, Pervyi Kanal and TNT TV were the
top four channels in both age categories, the data show. Fifth
Channel was the fifth-most watched among viewers 18 years and
older.  To contact the reporter on this story:
